SIMPLE: reconvey
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reconvey
<hw>Re`con*vey"</hw> <pr>(-v?")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To convey back or to the former place; <as>as, to <ex>reconvey</ex>
goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To transfer back to a former owner; <as>as, to
<ex>reconvey</ex> an estate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reconveyance</ent>⟦br⟧
